\section{Introduction}

The Haiphen Intelligence Platform employs a six-service analysis pipeline to assess
infrastructure risk. Each signal is processed through independent evaluation modules,
and the aggregate risk score $R$ is computed as:

\begin{equation}
R = \sum_{i=1}^{6} w_i \cdot S_i
\end{equation}

\noindent where $w_i$ represents the signal-type-specific weight for service $i$ and $S_i$ is the
service score (0--100). For the primary signal type \textit{ {{- escape .PrimarySignalType -}} },
the top-weighted services are {{.TopWeightedServices}}.

